      "Students of Quantum Cosmo School in Lama, Bandarban proudly secured first place again in the National Children's Parade, achieving their fourth consecutive victory. The event, organized by the Dhaka District Administration on 26 March 2018 to commemorate Independence Day, was held at Bangabandhu National Stadium. The Prime Minister of Bangladesh, Sheikh Hasina, attended as the chief guest.\n\nVarious schools participated in the colorful parade, saluting the Prime Minister, who received the salute and observed the performances. This year, 49 schools and children's organizations from across the country joined the march-past. The Quantum Cosmo students performed in two groupsтАФsmall and largeтАФconsisting of 66 parade members. Their unique costumes, confident gestures, and impressive performance drew everyone's attention. Additionally, 176 students participated in the school's band, captivating the audience, including the Prime Minister.\n\nQuantum Cosmo School had previously participated for the first time in 2015 and secured first place, maintaining a winning streak to the present. This year, BAF Shaheen College was second, and Government Children's Home was third. Awards were received from the Minister for Liberation War Affairs, A K M Mozammel Haque, and Dhaka District Commissioner Abu Saleh Mohammad Ferdous Khan.\n\nFounded in 2001 under the Quantum Foundation in the remote area of Lama, Bandarban, the school began with only seven children and now has over 1,500 students. The institution aims to develop underprivileged children into enlightened individuals, demonstrating that with proper guidance, they can excel academically, athletically, and socially.",
